{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id79672d1f-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1171"},"text":"§ 1171.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Definitions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"As used in this chapter—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79672d20-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" The term “gambling device” means—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79672d21-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any so-called “slot machine” or any other machine or mechanical device an essential part of which is a drum or reel with insignia thereon, and (A) which when operated may deliver, as the result of the application of an element of chance, any money or property, or (B) by the operation of which a person may become entitled to receive, as the result of the application of an element of chance, any money or property; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79672d22-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any other machine or mechanical device (including, but not limited to, roulette wheels and similar devices) designed and manufactured primarily for use in connection with gambling, and (A) which when operated may deliver, as the result of the application of an element of chance, any money or property, or (B) by the operation of which a person may become entitled to receive, as the result of the application of an element of chance, any money or property; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79672d23-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171/a/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" any subassembly or essential part intended to be used in connection with any such machine or mechanical device, but which is not attached to any such machine or mechanical device as a constituent part.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79672d24-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “State” includes the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands, and Guam.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79672d25-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “possession of the United States” means any possession of the United States which is not named in paragraph ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn002303"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn002303"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" So in original. Probably should be “subsection”."}],"tail":" (b) of this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79672d26-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171/d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"d"},"text":"(d)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “interstate or foreign commerce” means commerce (1) between any State or possession of the United States and any place outside of such State or possession, or (2) between points in the same State or possession of the United States but through any place outside thereof.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79672d27-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171/e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"e"},"text":"(e)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “intrastate commerce” means commerce wholly within one State or possession of the United States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79672d28-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0","identifier":"/us/usc/t15/s1171/f"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"f"},"text":"(f)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “boundaries” has the same meaning given that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s1301"},"text":"section 1301 of title 43","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id79672d29-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1951-01-02/ch1194/s1"},"text":"Jan. 2, 1951, ch. 1194, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1134"},"text":"64 Stat. 1134","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/840"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–840","children":[],"tail":", §§ 2, 3, "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/1075"},"text":"76 Stat. 1075","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/251/tII/s202/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–251, title II, § 202(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-03-09"},"text":"Mar. 9, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/62"},"text":"106 Stat. 62","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id79672d2a-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id79672d2b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id79672d2c-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1992—Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/251"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–251","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1962—Subsec. (a)(2), (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/840/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–840, § 2","children":[],"tail":", substituted provisions including machines and mechanical devices designed and manufactured primarily for gambling by the operation of which a person may become entitled to receive, as the result of chance, any money or property, for provisions which included machines or mechanical devices designed and manufactured to operate by inserting a coin, token, or similar object, in par. (2), and inserted “, but which is not attached to any such machine or mechanical device as a constituent part”, in par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/840/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–840, § 3","children":[],"tail":", substituted “the District of Columbia” for “Alaska, Hawaii”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsecs. (d), (e). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/840/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–840, § 3","children":[],"tail":", added subsecs. (d) and (e)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id79672d2d-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id79672d2e-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1962 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/840/s7"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–840, § 7","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/1077"},"text":"76 Stat. 1077","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/87/840/s7"},"text":"“The amendments made by this Act [enacting ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1178"},"text":"section 1178 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and amending this section and sections 1172 and 1173 of this title] shall take effect on the sixtieth day after the date of its enactment ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1962","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitleOfAmendment","id":"id79672d2f-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title of 1962 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/87/840/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 87–840, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1962-10-18"},"text":"Oct. 18, 1962","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/76/1075"},"text":"76 Stat. 1075","children":[],"tail":", provided: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/87/840/s1"},"text":"“That this Act [enacting ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1178"},"text":"section 1178 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and amending this section and sections 1172 and 1173 of this title] may be cited as the ‘Gambling Devices Act of 1962’.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"id79672d30-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1951-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 1951","children":[],"tail":", which enacted this chapter and a note set out under this section, is popularly known as the “Gambling Devices Transportation Act”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"separability","id":"id79672d31-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Separability","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1951-01-02/ch1194/s8"},"text":"Act Jan. 2, 1951, ch. 1194, § 8","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/64/1136"},"text":"64 Stat. 1136","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/act/1951-01-02/ch1194/s8"},"text":"“If any provision of this Act [this chapter] or the application thereof to any person or circumstance is held invalid, such invalidity shall not affect other provisions or applications of the Act [this chapter] which can be given effect without the invalid provision or application, and to this end the provisions of this Act [this chapter] are declared to be severable.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
